The Chronicle Sukulwenkosi Dube- Matutu, Online Reporter TWO-gun brandishing men attacked a family and stole US$1 040 and R810 among other valuables. Police on their Twitter page confirmed the incident which occurred in Masvingo on May 18 around 3AM. “Police in Masvingo are investigating a robbery case which occurred on 18 May 2022 at around 3AM at Watungwa Village, Madamombe Mashava. Two suspects who were armed with a pistol attacked a man (59) and his son (34). The duo stole US$1040 and R 810 cash as well as six cellphones. Anyone with information to contact any nearest Police Station, ” said the police. @DubeMatutu